    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fæzǧær" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>fæzǧær</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense n="1" xml:id="sense_fæzǧær.1"><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>большой кусок</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>big piece</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>глыба</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>lump</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <sense n="2" xml:id="sense_fæzǧær.2"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>сот</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>cell</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>(wæjg˳ytæ) bæstæ æmæ xæxtæ raxæssync semæ fæzǧærgaj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>(великаны) глыбами рушат за собой землю и горы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>giants crush the earth and mountains behind them with boulders</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            20</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mydy fæzǧær</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сот с медом</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>honeycomb</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из %ifæ-zǧær%i ← %ipati-zgar-%i? Во второй части совпали,
                    возможно, две разных основы: 1. %i*zǧar-%i ← %i*ǧzar-%i, см. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7ǧzalyn"/> ‘сыпать’, отсюда значение ‘кусок’, ‘глыба’; 2.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zgar"/> ‘округлость’, ‘углубление’ (<mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>zgərəsna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>округлый</q></gloss></mentioned>), отсюда — ‘сот’. %bИнг.%b
                        <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>fæskæl</w>
                        <gloss><q>сот</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><biblScope>Caucasica XI
                            61</biblScope></bibl>) следует считать усвоенным из осетинского, так как
                    фонема %if%i чужда искони вейнахским языкам (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru"
                            >Языки Сев. Кавказа и Дагестана I 104 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">Languages of the North Caucasus and Dagestan I 104
                            ff.</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">From %ifæ-zǧær%i ← %ipati-zgar-%i? In the second part, perhaps
                    two different stems coincided: 1. %i*zǧar-%i ← %i*ǧzar-%i, see <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7ǧzalyn"/> ‘pour’, from which there is the meaning ‘piece’,
                    ‘boulder’; 2. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zgar"/> ‘circularity’, ‘deepening’
                        (<mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>zgərəsna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>rounded</q></gloss></mentioned>), from which there is the meaning
                    ‘cell’. <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>fæskæl</w>
                        <gloss><q>cell</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><biblScope>Caucasica XI
                            61</biblScope></bibl>) should be considered as acquired from Ossetic,
                    since the phoneme %if%i is alien from time immemorial to the Weinakh languages
                            (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="en">Languages of the North Caucasus
                            and Dagestan I 104 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
            </entry>
